rsFt1MIB.contactinfo: Redstone Communications, Inc. 5 Carlisle Road Westford MA 01886 USA Tel: +1-978-692-1999 Email: mib@redstonecom.com
rsFt1MIB.description: The Fractional T1 MIB for the Redstone Communications Inc. enterprise.

rsFt1NextIfIndex.name: rsFt1NextIfIndex
rsFt1NextIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in rsFt1IfTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

rsFt1IfTable.name: rsFt1IfTable
rsFt1IfTable.description: This table contains entries for FT1 interfaces present in the system.

rsFt1IfEntry.name: rsFt1IfEntry
rsFt1IfEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of an FT1 interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created /deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/rsIfTable.

rsFt1IfIndex.name: rsFt1IfIndex
rsFt1IfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the FT1 interface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading rsFt1NextIfIndex.

rsFt1IfRowStatus.name: rsFt1IfRowStatus
rsFt1IfRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: rsFt1IfRowStatus rsFt1IfLowerIfIndex rsFt1IfTimeSlotMap In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: A value for rsFt1IfIndex must have been determined previously, by reading rsFt1NextIfIndex. The DS1 interface identified by rsFt1IfLowerIfIndex must exist. The DS0s specified in rsFt1IfTimeSlotMap must be available (unallocated) on the DS1 interface identified by rsFt1IfLowerIfIndex. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/rsIfTable is created/destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

rsFt1IfLowerIfIndex.name: rsFt1IfLowerIfIndex
rsFt1IfLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of a DS1 interface over which this FT1 interface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a nonzero value be configured at entry creation.

rsFt1IfTimeSlotMap.name: rsFt1IfTimeSlotMap
rsFt1IfTimeSlotMap.description: A bitmap representing the DS0s on the underlying DS1 interface that have been allocated to this FT1 interface.

rsFt1IfTimeSlotRate.name: rsFt1IfTimeSlotRate
rsFt1IfTimeSlotRate.description: Data rate per time slot allocated to this FT1 interface.

rsFt1IfDataPolarity.name: rsFt1IfDataPolarity
rsFt1IfDataPolarity.description: Polarity of data transmitted on this FT1 interface. Inverted data is used for certain line coding configurations to ensure sufficient one's density for timing recovery by the remote end.

rsFt1IfLoopbackConfig.name: rsFt1IfLoopbackConfig
rsFt1IfLoopbackConfig.description: Selects loopback configuration. loop(1) causes received data to be looped back out the transmitter.

rsFt1Compliance.name: rsFt1Compliance
rsFt1Compliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Redstone FT1 MIB.

rsFt1Compliance2.name: rsFt1Compliance2
rsFt1Compliance2.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Redstone FT1 MIB.

rsFt1Group.name: rsFt1Group
rsFt1Group.description: A collection of objects providing management of FT1 interfaces in a Redstone product.
